<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,613,1178]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,410,613,638]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
: With the character states of Asiatic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[827,924,613,638]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[827,924,613,638]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Calleida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the widest sense, see above), restricted as follows: abdominal sternum VII with four or more setae in males (two or more on each side), six or more setae in females (three or more on each side); sternum VII notched in males (
<figureCitation box="[980,1091,685,710]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1664,1686]" captionTargetBox="[216,1350,195,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[216,1350,195,1626]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Characters of Calleida spp. 1–3 sternum VII of males: 1 C. cf. splendidula (Guangdong, China), [apex notched, one seta on each side]; 2 C. fukiensis (Fujian, China), [apex notched, two setae on each side]; 3 C. puncticollis sp. n. (Holotype, Hubei, China), [apex straight, four setae on each side]. 4–6 sternum VII of females: 4 C. cf. splendidula (Guangdong, China), [two setae on each side]; 5 C. fukiensis (Shaanxi, China), [three setae on each side]; 6 C. puncticollis sp. n. (Hubei, China), [six and seven setae on each side]. 7–9 basal three antennomeres: 7 C. gressittiana sp. n. (Holotype), [with sparse additional setae]; 8 C. excelsa (Yunnan, China), [with dense additional setae]; 9 C. borneensis sp. n. (Sabah, Malaysia), [without additional setae]. 10 elytral shoulder, C. sultana (Yunnan, China), [humeral margins setose]. 11–14 pronotal anterior angle: 11 C. gressittiana sp. n. (Holotype), [with erect setae]; 12 C. excelsa (Yunnan, China), [with erect setae]; 13 C. sultana (Yunnan, China), [with erect setae]; 14 C. borneensis sp. n. (Sabah, Malaysia), [without setae]. 15–18 elytral outer apical angle: 15 C. corporaali (Sabah, Malaysia), [acute, forming sharp tooth]; 16 C. borneensis sp. n. (Sabah, Malaysia), [markedly widened, not forming tooth]; 17 C. doriae (Yunnan, China), [slightly widened]; 18 C. gressittiana sp. n. (Holotype), [completely round, not widened]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1302715/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">figs. 2, 5</figureCitation>
); endophallus with two short copulatory pieces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,613,1178]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,388,757,782]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Taxonomic note</emphasis>
: Two already described species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Heller" authorityName="Heller in Mindanao" authorityYear="1921" box="[758,989,757,782]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discoidalis">
<emphasis box="[758,912,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">C. discoidalis</emphasis>
Heller
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Jedlicka" authorityName="Jedlicka" authorityYear="1953" box="[1044,1276,757,782]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fukiensis">
<emphasis box="[1044,1174,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">C. fukiensis</emphasis>
Jedlička
</taxonomicName>
, are attributed to this group, and several new species will be described in our next contribution (Shi &amp; Casale, submitted). Species of this group are distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[498,568,829,854]" name="China" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[579,636,830,853]" name="Laos" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Laos</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[647,742,829,854]" name="Vietnam" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[796,926,829,854]" name="Philippines" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Philippines</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,613,1178]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This species group is very probably not monophyletic, and relationships amongst species are unclear. In species of this group the only similarity is the presence of two short copulatory pieces in endophallus, a character common with many Asiatic, African and Madagascan 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[776,872,937,962]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[776,872,937,962]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Calleida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. The group is so far defined by one only external morphological feature (abdominal sternum VII multisetose), which could be demonstrated as not synapomorphic in the Asiatic species: in fact, this character is also present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[1029,1126,1009,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1126,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Calleida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of several different groups in Africa, Madagascar and the Neotropical Region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,613,1178]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Nevertheless, at moment the multiple setation of the abdominal sternum VII is a valid diagnostic feature able to isolate this “group of convenience” from all other species of Asia (except the 
<taxonomicName box="[1054,1185,1117,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticollis">
<emphasis box="[1054,1185,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">puncticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, treated before).
</paragraph>
